{"title_page": "CAA Art Museum", "text_new": "{{Infobox museum\n| name = CAA Art Museum\n| native_name = {{lang-zh|\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986}}<br />CAA Art Museum\n| logo = \n| image = \n| map_type = \n| former_name = \n| established = {{Start date and age|1935|p=yes}}\n| location = 218 Nanshan Rd, Shangcheng District, Hangzhou, Zhejiang, China\n| coordinates = {{Coord|30.24451|N|120.15474|E|display=inline,title}}\n| type = [[Art Museum]]\n| collections = \n| visitors = \n| director = \n| chairperson = [[Hang Jian]]\n| architect = \n| publictransit = [[Hangzhou Metro]] [[Dingan Road Station]]\n| website = {{URL|https://caam.caa.edu.cn/gymsg/msgjs|\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986}}\n| imagesize = \n}}'''CAA Art Museum''' ({{Zh|c=|s=\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986|t=\u4e2d\u570b\u7f8e\u8853\u5b78\u9662\u7f8e\u8853\u9928|p=Zh\u014dnggu\u00f3 m\u011bish\u00f9 xu\u00e9yu\u00e0n m\u011bish\u00f9gu\u01cen}}), is an [[art museum]] affiliated to [[China Academy of Art|China Art Academy]] (CAA) in [[Hangzhou]], [[Zhejiang]], [[China]]. Despite its history dating back to 1935, the Museum became open to the public in 2003 after its building was reconstructed.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite journal|author=\u9ec4\u8273|year=2012|others=|title=\u9ad8\u6821\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u5728\u827a\u672f\u9662\u6821\u6559\u80b2\u53d1\u5c55\u4e2d\u7684\u4f5c\u7528\u2014\u2014\u4ee5\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u4e3a\u4f8b|url=http://www.wanfangdata.com.cn/details/detail.do?_type=perio&id=msjyyj201211035|journal=\u7f8e\u672f\u6559\u80b2\u7814\u7a76|volume=|issue=11|page=2|doi=10.3969/j.issn.1674-9286.2012.11.035|pmid=}}</ref> Now, the museum comprises three sub-museum, including the Art Museum, the Design Museum and the Folk Crafts Museum.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/china-academy-of-fine-arts-mcacaa|title=Museum of Contemporary Art, China Art Academy|website=Google Arts & Culture|language=en|access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref> In 2015, the museum was listed among the 13 key art museums of China by the [[Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture]].<ref>{{Cite journal|author=\u9648\u5ca9|year=2015|others=|title=\u6587\u5316\u90e8\u7ec4\u7ec7\u5f00\u5c55\u5e76\u5b8c\u6210\u7b2c\u4e8c\u6b21\u5168\u56fd\u91cd\u70b9\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u8bc4\u4f30|url=http://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTotal-MEIS201512005.htm|journal=\u7f8e\u672f|volume=|issue=12|page=|doi=|pmid=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe history of the museum can date back to 1935 when a Russian professor, whose name was Dufei (\u675c\u98de) in Chinese, designed and supervised the construction of an gallery for the academy at a total cost of 30,000 Silver Yuan. The gallery replaced where used to be the Zhaodan Platform (\u7167\u80c6\u53f0) and Sanxian Temple (\u4e09\u8d24\u7960) near the West Lake and was one of the best gallery in China at that time. In 1949, it held the first National Exhibition of Fine Arts.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\nIn 2003, the building of the museum on Nanshan Road was rebuilt and renamed to Art Museum. Since then, it became open to the public and over 500 exhibitions have been held in the building. In 2015, the Folk Crafts Museum, one of the sub-museum of the CAA Art Museum, which focused on ethnic and folk arts, located in Xiangshan Campus came into use. In 2017, China Design Museum, another sub-museum,  became open to the public.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://caam.caa.edu.cn/gymsg/msgjs/|title=\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u4ecb\u7ecd|author=|date=|work=\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986|publisher=|language=|format=|accessdate=2019-08-13}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[China Academy of Art]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/china-academy-of-fine-arts-mcacaa?hl=en Museum of Contemporary Art, China Art Academy], [[Google Arts & Culture]].\n* [http://shadow.caa.edu.cn/#/ Digital Museum of Shadow], CAA Art Museum.\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Museums in Hangzhou]]\n[[Category:Art museums and galleries in China]]\n[[Category:Asian art museums]]\n[[Category:Art museums established in 1935]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 2003]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox museum\n| name = CAA Art Museum\n| native_name = {{lang-zh|\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986}}<br />CAA Art Museum\n| logo = \n| image = \n| map_type = \n| former_name = \n| established = {{Start date and age|1935|p=yes}}\n| location = 218 Nanshan Rd, Shangcheng District, Hangzhou, Zhejiang, China\n| coordinates = {{Coord|30.24451|N|120.15474|E|display=inline,title}}\n| type = [[Art Museum]]\n| collections = \n| visitors = \n| director = \n| chairperson = [[Hang Jian]]\n| architect = \n| publictransit = [[Hangzhou Metro]] [[Dingan Road Station]]\n| website = {{URL|https://caam.caa.edu.cn/gymsg/msgjs|\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986}}\n| imagesize = \n}}'''CAA Art Museum''' ({{Zh|c=|s=\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986|t=\u4e2d\u570b\u7f8e\u8853\u5b78\u9662\u7f8e\u8853\u9928|p=Zh\u014dnggu\u00f3 m\u011bish\u00f9 xu\u00e9yu\u00e0n m\u011bish\u00f9gu\u01cen}}), is an [[art museum]] affiliated to [[China Academy of Art|China Art Academy]] (CAA) in [[Hangzhou]], [[Zhejiang]], [[China]]. Despite its history dating back to 1935, the Museum became open to the public in 2003 after its building was reconstructed.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite journal|author=\u9ec4\u8273|year=2012|others=|title=\u9ad8\u6821\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u5728\u827a\u672f\u9662\u6821\u6559\u80b2\u53d1\u5c55\u4e2d\u7684\u4f5c\u7528\u2014\u2014\u4ee5\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u4e3a\u4f8b|url=http://www.wanfangdata.com.cn/details/detail.do?_type=perio&id=msjyyj201211035|journal=\u7f8e\u672f\u6559\u80b2\u7814\u7a76|volume=|issue=11|page=2|doi=10.3969/j.issn.1674-9286.2012.11.035|pmid=}}</ref> Now, the museum comprises three sub-museum, including the Art Museum, the Design Museum and the Folk Crafts Museum.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/china-academy-of-fine-arts-mcacaa|title=Museum of Contemporary Art, China Art Academy|website=Google Arts & Culture|language=en|access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref> In 2015, the museum was listed among the 13 key art museums of China by the [[Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture]].<ref>{{Cite journal|author=\u9648\u5ca9|year=2015|others=|title=\u6587\u5316\u90e8\u7ec4\u7ec7\u5f00\u5c55\u5e76\u5b8c\u6210\u7b2c\u4e8c\u6b21\u5168\u56fd\u91cd\u70b9\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u8bc4\u4f30|url=http://www.cnki.com.cn/Article/CJFDTotal-MEIS201512005.htm|journal=\u7f8e\u672f|volume=|issue=12|page=|doi=|pmid=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe history of the museum can date back to 1935 when a Russian professor, whose name was Dufei (\u675c\u98de) in Chinese, designed and supervised the construction of an gallery for the academy at a total cost of 30,000 Silver Yuan. The gallery replaced where used to be the Zhaodan Platform (\u7167\u80c6\u53f0) and Sanxian Temple (\u4e09\u8d24\u7960) near the West Lake and was one of the best gallery in China at that time. In 1949, it held the first National Exhibition of Fine Arts.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\nIn 2003, the building of the museum on Nanshan Road was rebuilt and renamed to Art Museum. Since then, it became open to the public and over 500 exhibitions have been held in the building. In 2015, the Folk Crafts Museum, one of the sub-museum of the CAA Art Museum, which focused on ethnic and folk arts, located in Xiangshan Campus came into use. In 2017, China Design Museum, another sub-museum,  became open to the public.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://caam.caa.edu.cn/gymsg/msgjs/|title=\u7f8e\u672f\u9986\u4ecb\u7ecd|author=|date=|work=\u4e2d\u56fd\u7f8e\u672f\u5b66\u9662\u7f8e\u672f\u9986|publisher=|language=|format=|accessdate=2019-08-13}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[China Academy of Art]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/china-academy-of-fine-arts-mcacaa?hl=en Museum of Contemporary Art, China Art Academy], [[Google Arts & Culture]].\n* [http://shadow.caa.edu.cn/#/ Digital Museum of Shadow], CAA Art Museum.\n\n[[Category:Museums in Hangzhou]]\n[[Category:Art museums and galleries in China]]\n[[Category:Asian art museums]]\n[[Category:Art museums established in 1935]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 2003]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAA_Art_Museum"}
